Food prices fell by 1.2% year-on-year in April after rising by 1.8% year-on-year in March. Non-food prices increased year-on-year by 0.8% in April compared with a rise of 1.1% a month earlier. On a month-on-month basis, the consumer price index rose 0.6% in April. Core annual inflation stood at 0.3% on a month-on-month basis and 1.1% year-on-year. The central bank expects inflation to drop to 0.6% in 2019 from 1.9% in 2018 before picking up to 1.1% in 2020. --Reuters--